&lt;p&gt;ICU / HDU - Radnor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Require Critical Care Assistants - Band 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;for part time work (minimum 69 hours over a 4 week rota) Long days and internal rotation onto night duty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Salisbury District Hospital NHS Foundation Trust Intensive Care and High Dependency Unit (Radnor) is a general 10 bedded critical care unit which also supports the regional referral centres for burns, plastics and spinal cord injuries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Critical Care Assistants preferably with previous health care experience to join our friendly team. You will need to have achieved GCSE grade A-C in Maths and English or level 2 equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires you to be a motivated and enthusiastic team member with basic IT skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to assist Registered Nurses with the care of critically ill patients, their families and their rehabilitation after acute illness. A significant proportion of the role also includes keeping the unit clean and tidy, ordering consumables and restocking the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a specialist assistant post and the successful candidate will be expected to undertake the competency based in house development programme and the National Care Certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron&#39;s Emily Rudd and Nick Hayter, Senior Staff Nurse Jennie Rennie&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01722 336262 x 4373&lt;/p&gt;
